            <h2>What is TOEFL iBT?</h2>
            <p>TOEFL iBT or TOEFL Internet-Based Test (TOEFL iBT) is the online version of the TOEFL test for candidates to appear in their exams. TOEFL iBT is the preferred version of TOEFL as it is more convenient and uses fewer resources. TOEFL test centers are authorized across the country with big cities to hold these TOEFL exams and TOEFL iBT is the most preferred mode of exam and represents about 98% of the TOEFL exam worldwide.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- TOEFL Syllabus Section -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <h2>TOEFL Syllabus 2024</h2>
            <p>The TOEFL exam syllabus has been designed primarily to assess the reading, writing, listening, and speaking skills of candidates in a setting of university. Given below is the TOEFL Exam format which covers the TOEFL syllabus for all 4 sections: Reading, Listening, Speaking and Writing:</p>
